  <title>Description</title>
  <titlealts>
    <searchtitle>Attribute: A AND E ATTENDANCE CATEGORY - Description</searchtitle>
  </titlealts>
  <body>

  <p>
An indication of whether a 
    <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENT</xref>
 is making first or follow-up attendance at a particular 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_accident_and_emergency_department">Accident and Emergency Department</xref>
.  </p>
  <p>
      <b>Note:</b>
  </p>
  <p>
An attendance at a 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_consultant_clinic">Consultant Clinic</xref>
 following an 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_accident_and_emergency_attendance">Accident and Emergency Attendance</xref>
 is an 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_out-patient_attendance_consultant">Out-Patient Attendance Consultant</xref>
 and not an 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_accident_and_emergency_attendance">Accident and Emergency Attendance</xref>
 even if the clinic may be held in or near the 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_accident_and_emergency_department">Accident and Emergency Department</xref>
, e.g. a Fracture Clinic.  </p>
